# SMC Commander Trading Engine -- Full Implementation Plan

## Dependency Graph (Build Order)

The following diagram shows module dependencies. Files must be built bottom-up: a module cannot be implemented until everything it depends on exists.

```
Layer 0 (no deps):     package.json, tsconfig.json
Layer 1 (config only):  src/core/errors.ts
Layer 2 (core types):   src/core/types.ts (depends on errors for doc references)
Layer 3 (constants):    src/core/constants.ts (depends on types)
Layer 4 (utilities):    src/utils/math.ts, src/utils/time.ts, src/utils/validation.ts (depend on types, constants, errors)
Layer 5 (analysis):     MarketStructure, LiquidityAnalyzer, EntryDetector, AMDDetector, KillZoneManager (depend on Layer 0-4)
Layer 6 (scoring):      SetupScorer, RiskCalculator, SessionManager (depend on analysis + core)
Layer 7 (engine):       SMCAnalyzer (depends on everything above)
Layer 8 (public API):   src/index.ts (re-exports)
Layer 9 (tests):        unit tests, integration tests, fixtures
```

