## Potential Challenges and Mitigations

| Challenge | Mitigation |
|-----------|------------|
| Asian session crossing midnight (20:00-00:00) | `isWithinKillZone` handles `startHour > endHour` with split logic |
| DST shifts affecting kill zone times | Use `date-fns-tz` which handles DST automatically; store times as EST concept, convert via library |
| FVG detection on gaps with spread | The `fvgMinSizeMultiplier * ATR` filter eliminates noise FVGs |
| Order Block detection requires looking backward from structure breaks | Pass `StructureBreak[]` into `EntryDetector.detectOrderBlocks()` and scan backward from each break index |
| Equal highs/lows detection sensitivity | Configurable `equalLevelTolerance` in pips; default `0.0003` for forex is approximately 3 pips |
| Circuit breaker state persistence across restarts | `SessionManager` is in-memory; document that consumers must persist `SessionState` if needed |
| HTF context requires separate data feed | `analyzeWithHTF()` accepts separate HTF candle array and runs `MarketStructure` analysis on it first |

